<br>
I would like to challenge you all with taking to ideals and goals you have made for yourself in DAoC and carry that mantle with you into the real world.<br>
<br>
You are a Silver Hawk.  In deed and action, you have proven yourself to be of better quality and nobility than others.<br>
<br>
How can we do this?  By abiding by the seven values that any Silver Hawk should adhere to:<br>
<br>
1. <b>Nobility</b> - Having or showing qualities of high moral character.<br>
<br>
2. <b>Honor</b> - Principled uprightness of character<br>
<br>
3. <b>Respect</b> - To feel or show deferential regard for<br>
<br>
4. <b>Loyalty</b> - A feeling or attitude of devoted attachment<br>
<br>
5. <b>Valor</b> - Courage and boldness, as in battle; bravery<br>
<br>
6. <b>Generosity</b> - Liberality in giving or willingness to give<br>
<br>
7. <b>Compassion</b> - Deep awareness of the suffering of another coupled with the wish to relieve it<br>
<br>
As you attend to your daily lives, in game and out, strive to uphold these virtues.  This world needs Knights, <b>Knights of the New Millennium</b>, to bring back the values and goals that this world lacks.  Someone needs help, lend it.  Someone needs protection, protect him or her.  Someone needs a hand, give it.  Someone needs understanding, bring it.<br>
<br>
I realize this is a mighty task.  It will mean vigilance and work as most good things do.  I know that not all of you can do this.  Not all of you have the strength it will take.<br>
<br>
Nevertheless, the challenge is made.  Let those who accept it and overcome it reap the bounty it will bring.<br>
