<br>
This is the reason it is said the Hawks are not an easy guild and we tell people that we aren't for everyone nor try to be.<br>
<br>
For myself, things that are achieved with ease end up not being worthwhile to have and keep.  There have been many times the hawks have brought me headache and angst... for it is the curse of one that cares.  One I think we all bare, in game or out.<br>
<br>
Despite all of this, at the end of the day I feel complete.  <br>
<br>
Tis is our duty to be resolvent in the face of the beligerants and miscreants and to always fight the good fight.<br>
<br>
Many times I have told myself, &quot;why do I put myself through this, why don't I just leave.  I could join an uber guild and go do epic raids etc. etc.&quot;  Well, I could never get myself to be that way and if I did go and do that... deep down inside I know I would not truly be happy.  I've seen other brothers and sisters go that way and they never seem to happy once they are gone... many of which come back.<br>
<br>
These games are not just about pixels of loot, they are about joining with other real human beings with whom you share thoughts and feelings.  They are about enjoying the impossible victory with those people, logging in to see familiar faces, and being there to support one another in times of need and grief.  Sharing a funny joke or joining together to help a stranger out.<br>
<br>
Thank you Hawks for being such fine folks to login and say hi to and to share all of those agonies of defeat and shouts of triumph victories.  I enjoy all my times with you all and appreciate your support as guild brothers and sisters.  I look forward to many great days for the Silver Hawks ahead.<br>
<br>
Thanks Fernus.  I think these virtues should become a part of the hawks creed.<br>
<br>
